You are supposed to put the _path_ of the UnityEngine.dll there, not just `UnityEngine.dll`, unless it exists in the working directory, which is highly unlikely.

According to [this answer](https://gamedev.stackexchange.com/questions/103302/where-are-the-files-unityengine-dll-and-unityeditor-dll-located-on-a-windows-fil), you can easily find UnityEngine.dll (and other dlls as well) in your file system. It is under `Editor\Data\Managed`, so you should write:

    parameters.ReferencedAssemblies.Add(@&quot;C:\\path\to\your\unity\installation\Editor\Data\Managed\UnityEngine.dll&quot;);

